Installation of Editor
>You can use vi or vim to edit the files
  VI or VIM Commands
  To edit a file press "Insert" Key
  To finish editing press "Esc" Key
  To write the file press ":w"
  To Exit the editor press ":q"
  You can also write and quit ":wq"

>Or you can use gedit editor
  File will open in a normal notepad format and you can edit it the same way you edit a word file.
  
To install editor:
>vi
  sudo apt-get install vi

>vim
  sudo apt-get install vim
  
>gedit
  sudo apt-get install gedit
  
Note: sometimes it is preinstalled, then you can directly start using it to edit the file.

  
